race.comment: IRISH CONSORT (2) progressed nicely last time out to finish just 1.1 lengths from the winner in third over 1065m at Wagga Riverside after being in contention on the bend. Finds a tougher race but this looks well within his grasp. ROWDY ANTHEM (3) finished out of the money two starts back then was beaten 3.5 lengths when sixth in a 1200m contest at Echuca four weeks ago. Best figures measure up nicely. Sure to run well. BRONCO REVOLUTION (12) is close to breaking through after three consecutive placings, the latest coming when third over 1100m at Gunbower. Suitably placed so anticipating another big run. EXCITING TIMES (13) was in the money two starts back at Warrnambool but was unable to repeat the effort last time when eighth, beaten 5 lengths, at Warrnambool over 1000m. Suitably placed so anticipating a better run this time.
